pa and Sonoma Valleys. M.F.K. Fisher was a solitary cook who interpreted the scenario of a meal in her own way, and M.F.K. Fisher among the Pots and Pans provides a deeply personal glimpse of a woman who continues to mystify even as she commands our attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aCooking. 0aFood writerszUnited StatesvBiography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Agriculture & Food (see also POLITICAL SCIENCE / Public Policy / Agriculture & Food Policy).2bisacsh  a1900s.  a20th century.  aacademic.  abiographical.  aboarding school.  achef.  acookbook.  acooking.  acuisine.  aculinary.  aeagle rock.  aeating.  afood lovers.  afood.  agastronomy.  ahistory buff.  akitchen setting.  akitchen.  alaguna beach.  alife story.  ascholarly.  athe art of eating.  athe boston cooking school cookbook.  athe settlement cookbook.  atrue story.  awhittier.  aworld history.1 aHesser, Amanda, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052025555540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093477140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520934771423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520934771/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY